1
00:00:22,022 --> 00:00:24,733
Help! Somebody, help! Please?

2
00:00:24,983 --> 00:00:27,569
All right, all right, relax, I'm back.

3
00:00:27,736 --> 00:00:30,030
What is this?

4
00:00:30,405 --> 00:00:32,157
How's his rash, need ointment?

5
00:00:32,324 --> 00:00:36,537
I don't know. I'm procrastinating.
It's not my favourite thing to check.

6
00:00:36,703 --> 00:00:39,081
You don't have a problem
checking Wyatt's.

7
00:00:39,248 --> 00:00:43,001
That's 'cause I don't flash forward
to Wyatt being 22 like I do Chris.

8
00:00:43,168 --> 00:00:45,963
Oh... yeah!

9
00:00:46,129 --> 00:00:48,674
Exactly. Stinky diaper!

10
00:00:51,343 --> 00:00:53,053
Hey, hey,
are you using magic?

11
00:00:53,220 --> 00:00:55,889
Yeah, wait till you see
how I put the ointment on.

12
00:00:56,056 --> 00:00:59,726
Hi! Personal gain. Do you wanna
lose your powers like Phoebe did?

13
00:00:59,893 --> 00:01:02,604
- What if a demon attacks?
- It'd liven things up.

14
00:01:02,771 --> 00:01:06,942
- Excuse me?
- I'm just kidding... sort of.

15
00:01:07,109 --> 00:01:10,320
I love being a stay-at-home auntie.
I really, really do.

16
00:01:10,487 --> 00:01:11,738
I just...

17
00:01:11,905 --> 00:01:13,991
I'm going crazy.
I have to get out.

18
00:01:14,157 --> 00:01:16,785
It wouldn't hurt you
to get out a little bit too.

19
00:01:16,952 --> 00:01:19,204
You've been
cooped up in here ever since...

20
00:01:21,582 --> 00:01:23,876
You know,
it's okay to talk about it, Piper.

21
00:01:24,042 --> 00:01:26,503
It won't hurt you.
It could even help.

22
00:01:26,670 --> 00:01:27,921
Talk about what?

23
00:01:28,088 --> 00:01:32,176
Gideon's gone, Chris and Wyatt
are safe. It all worked out.

24
00:01:32,759 --> 00:01:34,845
Oh, coffee, coffee, coffee.

25
00:01:35,012 --> 00:01:37,848
I cannot believe
how late for work I am again.

26
00:01:38,015 --> 00:01:39,141
'Morning to you too.

27
00:01:39,308 --> 00:01:43,187
If you could be dressed for the wedding,
when I come back, I'll honk,

28
00:01:43,353 --> 00:01:45,731
and you guys can come
meet me outside, okay?

29
00:01:45,898 --> 00:01:47,316
Wait, what?!

30
00:01:47,482 --> 00:01:49,568
Wait! What wedding?

31
00:01:49,735 --> 00:01:51,153
- Wedding?
- Christy's.

32
00:01:51,320 --> 00:01:55,365
- Piper, don't tell me you forgot.
- Christy's wedding, that's today?

33
00:01:56,742 --> 00:01:58,452
Well, I can't go. The kids...

34
00:01:58,619 --> 00:02:01,872
Actually, the kids were invited too.
So you can go.

35
00:02:02,039 --> 00:02:04,082
I think it would be good for them.

36
00:02:04,249 --> 00:02:08,962
- I think it'd be good for all of us.
- No, I can't go. The baby...

37
00:02:09,129 --> 00:02:12,841
Needs to be exposed to a germ or two,
get out of the house, you know,

38
00:02:13,008 --> 00:02:15,594
- build up his immune system.
- He's too young.

39
00:02:15,761 --> 00:02:18,847
- He's two months old.
- I know how old he is, thank you.

40
00:02:19,932 --> 00:02:23,519
Look, you can't protect them
from the big, bad world forever.

41
00:02:23,685 --> 00:02:26,813
They are going to have
to leave the house at some point.

42
00:02:27,231 --> 00:02:29,566
By the way, how's Leo doing?

43
00:02:29,900 --> 00:02:33,946
Well, considering who betrayed him,
he's doing as well as can be expected.

44
00:02:41,745 --> 00:02:43,413
I know you're here, Barbas.

45
00:02:45,082 --> 00:02:46,834
You can't keep running from me!

46
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:50,546
You're afraid that vanquishing me
won't ease your pain...

47
00:02:51,088 --> 00:02:54,091
...because it wasn't a demon,
it was an Elder.

48
00:02:54,258 --> 00:02:57,636
Your very mentor
who tried to kill your son.

49
00:02:57,803 --> 00:03:01,515
You helped him.
That's why I'm gonna kill you too.

50
00:03:03,475 --> 00:03:04,643
Barbas!

51
00:03:24,538 --> 00:03:26,206
Zola?

52
00:03:28,375 --> 00:03:32,588
- Leo. Good, I've been calling for you.
- What do you mean, where's Barbas?

53
00:03:32,754 --> 00:03:35,340
- Who?
- He's covering up for me.

54
00:03:35,507 --> 00:03:38,552
Oh, you know he is.
You tracked me here.

55
00:03:38,719 --> 00:03:42,222
- What's the matter? You all right?
- One of your greatest fears.

56
00:03:42,389 --> 00:03:45,934
The good guys, the bad guys,
they're all the same now.

57
00:03:46,101 --> 00:03:50,606
Hey, that makes him just like Gideon.

58
00:03:51,356 --> 00:03:53,066
Leo, what are you doing?

59
00:03:54,610 --> 00:03:56,820
- Where's Barbas?
- I don't know!

60
00:03:56,987 --> 00:03:59,740
- Tell me!
- I don't know. For God sakes, stop!

61
00:04:07,247 --> 00:04:10,334
Damn. So close!

62
00:05:23,115 --> 00:05:24,783
Hey, have you seen Piper?

63
00:05:24,950 --> 00:05:28,829
- Up in Wyatt's room.
- I'm sorry, sweetie, were you sleeping?

64
00:05:30,706 --> 00:05:32,332
Why start now?

65
00:05:32,499 --> 00:05:36,753
No, I was actually just trying to
take a little break from nanny duties.

66
00:05:36,920 --> 00:05:39,506
You're a doll
to help out like you've been.

67
00:05:40,382 --> 00:05:43,093
I wish I could help you,
but I can't. I have to work.

68
00:05:43,260 --> 00:05:45,137
Tell me what it's like,

69
00:05:45,304 --> 00:05:48,557
out there in the world where
men don't poop or spit on you.

70
00:05:49,850 --> 00:05:51,435
You really do need to get out.

71
00:05:52,686 --> 00:05:55,439
You know, maybe we can
just swap jobs for the day.

72
00:05:55,606 --> 00:05:57,691
- You know, I'll... I'll pay you.
- Yeah?

73
00:05:58,609 --> 00:05:59,943
Don't tempt me.

74
00:06:01,862 --> 00:06:03,530
What, you're miserable too?

75
00:06:03,697 --> 00:06:06,200
No, I wouldn't say miserable.
I don't know,

76
00:06:06,366 --> 00:06:10,495
I can't put my finger on it.
I'm, like, in this rut or something.

77
00:06:10,662 --> 00:06:13,123
You know?
I just feel really disconnected.

78
00:06:13,290 --> 00:06:14,833
Yeah, I agree.

79
00:06:15,000 --> 00:06:18,295
You agree?
What do you know about my ruts?

80
00:06:18,462 --> 00:06:21,256
Well, I know you
gave some great advice to

81
00:06:21,423 --> 00:06:23,800
Lost in Los Altos
about finding new love.

82
00:06:23,967 --> 00:06:28,055
But you gave the same advice
to Dumped in Daly last year.

83
00:06:28,222 --> 00:06:30,307
What? Shut up, I did not!

84
00:06:30,474 --> 00:06:32,392
Are you kidding?

85
00:06:34,645 --> 00:06:36,855
Oh, my God, I did.

86
00:06:39,775 --> 00:06:43,612
Maybe I should stop giving
advice to people on finding love

87
00:06:43,779 --> 00:06:46,323
until I can figure out
how to find it myself.

88
00:06:46,490 --> 00:06:49,660
- You'll find it. You foresaw it.
- That was one big tease.

89
00:06:49,826 --> 00:06:51,912
- That's what's messing me up.
- No.

90
00:06:52,079 --> 00:06:54,248
I think what's
messing you up is Gideon.

91
00:06:54,414 --> 00:06:56,625
It's the thing that's
messing us all up.

92
00:06:56,792 --> 00:06:59,419
He didn't just betray Leo.
He betrayed all of us.

93
00:06:59,962 --> 00:07:02,714
And those wounds don't heal easily.

94
00:07:06,760 --> 00:07:08,262
Forgive the intrusion.

95
00:07:08,428 --> 00:07:11,849
- I thought it best I come to you first.
- We're not interested.

96
00:07:12,015 --> 00:07:15,435
I think you'll be interested in this.
Leo just tried to kill me.

97
00:07:15,602 --> 00:07:19,690
I didn't want other Elders to find out.
They'd think he was after us all.

98
00:07:19,857 --> 00:07:21,066
Can hardly blame him.

99
00:07:21,233 --> 00:07:24,570
Lack of faith's understandable
given what Gideon's done.

100
00:07:24,736 --> 00:07:26,989
But one bad Elder
doesn't make us all bad.

101
00:07:27,155 --> 00:07:29,449
- We are on the same side here.
- Are we?

102
00:07:29,616 --> 00:07:32,536
Leo didn't really want to kill me,
I know that.

103
00:07:32,703 --> 00:07:35,289
If he had, there'd
have been no redeeming him.

104
00:07:35,455 --> 00:07:39,126
- He would've had to have been recycled.
- Recycled like plastic?

105
00:07:39,293 --> 00:07:43,672
No, I mean sent back, reborn.
To start the cycle of life over again.

106
00:07:45,299 --> 00:07:47,843
We don't wanna punish him
for killing Gideon,

107
00:07:48,010 --> 00:07:51,555
but we can't abide his harming
innocents in the name of revenge.

108
00:07:51,722 --> 00:07:54,224
If you don't stop him,
we'll have to.

109
00:07:54,391 --> 00:07:57,644
- From what?
- His obsession with vanquishing Barbas.

110
00:07:58,312 --> 00:08:01,440
It's blinding him to reason,
driving him over the edge.

111
00:08:01,607 --> 00:08:05,944
And if he succeeds,
it won't make his sons any safer

112
00:08:06,320 --> 00:08:08,655
or the betrayal any less painful.

113
00:08:08,822 --> 00:08:10,240
It won't heal his heart.

114
00:08:11,658 --> 00:08:13,285
Time is of the essence too.

115
00:08:13,452 --> 00:08:14,995
Not just for his sake.

116
00:08:15,162 --> 00:08:18,040
There's a powerful threat
looming on the horizon,

117
00:08:18,207 --> 00:08:20,626
unlike any we've ever sensed before.

118
00:08:20,792 --> 00:08:23,921
And for that, we'll need
everybody back into the fold,

119
00:08:24,087 --> 00:08:25,964
and soon.

120
00:08:35,933 --> 00:08:37,601
Barbas?

121
00:08:41,355 --> 00:08:43,565
I know you're here.

122
00:08:43,732 --> 00:08:45,442
Show yourself.

123
00:08:45,609 --> 00:08:48,320
Don't let Barbas get away.

124
00:08:50,364 --> 00:08:52,741
Save your son.

125
00:08:54,743 --> 00:08:58,413
- Who are you? What do you want?
- Who are you talking to?

126
00:08:59,998 --> 00:09:02,292
Nobody.
How'd you know I was here?

127
00:09:02,459 --> 00:09:04,878
I didn't. Wyatt did.

128
00:09:05,087 --> 00:09:07,589
Must be that orbing thing
you guys share.

129
00:09:07,756 --> 00:09:09,925
He looked up and said, "Da-da."

130
00:09:10,092 --> 00:09:11,343
Really?

131
00:09:12,845 --> 00:09:15,848
He misses you. We all do.

132
00:09:16,181 --> 00:09:17,933
I miss him too. I...

133
00:09:18,100 --> 00:09:21,395
Is there anything else on Barbas
besides the main entry?

134
00:09:21,562 --> 00:09:23,689
No. Would you
like to hold your child?

135
00:09:26,900 --> 00:09:28,819
I can't.

136
00:09:30,070 --> 00:09:31,864
Well, you need to, Leo.

137
00:09:32,030 --> 00:09:35,325
Chris didn't die. He's alive.

138
00:09:36,785 --> 00:09:37,995
You need to move on.

139
00:09:38,161 --> 00:09:41,874
Not until Barbas is gone
and they're both safe.

140
00:09:48,297 --> 00:09:51,258
Is this absolutely necessary?

141
00:09:51,425 --> 00:09:56,013
The wound is deep.
It very easily could've been fatal.

142
00:09:56,180 --> 00:10:01,351
I wouldn't recommend going up
against an Elder again, if I were you.

143
00:10:01,560 --> 00:10:04,354
The problem is that
he's the one after me,

144
00:10:04,521 --> 00:10:07,107
and I haven't figured out
how to shake him.

145
00:10:08,358 --> 00:10:12,613
In that case, then,
this might all be for naught.

146
00:10:13,113 --> 00:10:15,908
Thank you very much
for your vote of confidence.

147
00:10:16,074 --> 00:10:18,952
Actually, I don't
even know what it is

148
00:10:19,119 --> 00:10:22,998
that I did to offend him,
except for that rug rat incident.

149
00:10:23,165 --> 00:10:26,168
And that all came out okay
in the end, more or less.

150
00:10:26,335 --> 00:10:29,171
And it wasn't even me
that was after them.

151
00:10:29,338 --> 00:10:31,423
But it should be now.

152
00:10:31,590 --> 00:10:33,926
Whoa, whoa, whoa!
What was that?

153
00:10:34,426 --> 00:10:37,304
- What was what?
- You didn't see that?

154
00:10:37,471 --> 00:10:39,264
See what?

155
00:10:39,431 --> 00:10:42,351
Go after the baby.

156
00:10:43,560 --> 00:10:45,437
That!

157
00:10:46,980 --> 00:10:48,106
What?

158
00:10:48,315 --> 00:10:52,486
He'll be blinded by rage, vulnerable.

159
00:10:53,862 --> 00:10:56,198
You trying to tell me
you didn't hear that?

160
00:10:57,574 --> 00:11:01,370
Maybe we should
look at that wound again.

161
00:11:01,537 --> 00:11:03,914
Oh, for God's sake.

162
00:11:06,708 --> 00:11:09,545
Was a rotten healer, anyway.

163
00:11:11,713 --> 00:11:13,882
Who are you?

164
00:11:14,049 --> 00:11:16,176
Friend or foe?

165
00:11:16,343 --> 00:11:19,888
Neither, but if you want
to stop the Elder,

166
00:11:20,055 --> 00:11:21,849
go after the baby!

167
00:11:28,605 --> 00:11:30,941
Cool.

168
00:11:31,108 --> 00:11:34,444
Very, very cool.

169
00:11:44,204 --> 00:11:46,415
- Phoebe, there you are.
- Elise, hi.

170
00:11:46,582 --> 00:11:49,042
I'm so sorry I'm late.
It won't happen again.

171
00:11:49,209 --> 00:11:50,419
Of course it will.

172
00:11:50,586 --> 00:11:53,672
But if you keep getting
responses like these, who cares?

173
00:11:53,839 --> 00:11:56,925
Look at these e-mails,
all from this morning's column.

174
00:11:57,092 --> 00:12:00,596
- About this morning's column...
- It was brilliant, Phoebe.

175
00:12:00,762 --> 00:12:03,682
I mean it, you make us
look classy when your advice is

176
00:12:03,849 --> 00:12:06,602
- provocative, insightful...
- Plagiarised?

177
00:12:06,768 --> 00:12:10,063
- Don't worry, I stole from myself.
- I don't understand.

178
00:12:10,230 --> 00:12:12,232
Yeah, I don't understand either.

179
00:12:12,399 --> 00:12:15,819
It turns out I gave the exact
same advice to someone last year.

180
00:12:15,986 --> 00:12:18,238
I didn't realise it
until it was too late.

181
00:12:19,198 --> 00:12:22,367
So? Big deal.
Columnists recycle stuff all the time.

182
00:12:22,534 --> 00:12:25,621
Yeah, but I don't.
At least, I never used to.

183
00:12:25,787 --> 00:12:27,581
And I just...

184
00:12:27,748 --> 00:12:31,752
I don't think I should write anymore
until I figure out why this happened.

185
00:12:31,919 --> 00:12:34,880
- Don't be ridiculous!
- No, I'm not being ridiculous.

186
00:12:35,047 --> 00:12:38,300
I'm being honest.
I can't give people recycled advice.

187
00:12:38,467 --> 00:12:41,470
It's... it's just not right.
It's not ethical.

188
00:12:41,637 --> 00:12:44,765
- Phoebe, you can't just quit.
- I don't wanna quit.

189
00:12:44,932 --> 00:12:47,935
Elise, I love my job, you know.

190
00:12:48,101 --> 00:12:50,521
I just don't think
that I can do it right now.

191
00:12:51,396 --> 00:12:54,441
Okay. All right.

192
00:12:54,608 --> 00:12:56,151
Take a sabbatical.

193
00:12:56,318 --> 00:12:59,530
Rest, recharge your batteries.
Couple of months enough?

194
00:12:59,696 --> 00:13:01,865
- Can I do that?
- Of course. I'm the boss.

195
00:13:02,032 --> 00:13:04,493
What happens to my column?
Do you pull it?

196
00:13:04,660 --> 00:13:07,079
And watch sales drop?
Are you kidding?

197
00:13:07,246 --> 00:13:11,041
No. I'll hire someone
to ghost-write it for you.

198
00:13:11,208 --> 00:13:13,418
Your readers'll
never know you're gone.

199
00:13:13,585 --> 00:13:14,670
Wait, what?

200
00:13:14,837 --> 00:13:18,090
Phoebe? Sorry, it's your sister.
She says it's important.

201
00:13:18,257 --> 00:13:21,343
Go ahead, I'll handle this.
Don't worry about anything.

202
00:13:21,510 --> 00:13:23,011
Rest up!

203
00:13:29,101 --> 00:13:30,352
Hello?

204
00:13:30,519 --> 00:13:34,064
Hey, I think I have
figured out how to save Leo.

205
00:13:34,231 --> 00:13:37,109
If we can keep him
from going after Barbas,

206
00:13:37,276 --> 00:13:39,236
then we can go after him ourselves.

207
00:13:39,403 --> 00:13:40,988
- Wait, what?
- It's perfect.

208
00:13:41,154 --> 00:13:44,199
All we do is guilt Leo
into taking Piper to the wedding.

209
00:13:44,366 --> 00:13:47,119
- She doesn't wanna go.
- That's why I'll volunteer

210
00:13:47,286 --> 00:13:51,081
to take the kids. That way, Piper
won't have any excuse not to go.

211
00:13:51,248 --> 00:13:55,085
While you're at the wedding, I'll be
at the Book trying to find Barbas.

212
00:13:55,252 --> 00:13:58,088
If we find him, how are we
gonna vanquish him without

213
00:13:58,255 --> 00:14:01,091
- my powers and Piper's?
- You can still cast spells.

214
00:14:01,258 --> 00:14:03,719
- Paige.
- I'm telling you, this could work.

215
00:14:03,886 --> 00:14:05,304
Not only could it save Leo,

216
00:14:05,470 --> 00:14:08,807
it can get him and Piper
back together, at a wedding no less.

217
00:14:08,974 --> 00:14:11,393
Think about it,
it could reignite sparks.

218
00:14:11,560 --> 00:14:13,478
You know, do it for the children.

219
00:14:13,645 --> 00:14:16,148
- Hell, do it for me.
- I don't know about this.

220
00:14:16,315 --> 00:14:18,859
Do you want to
get out of that rut or don't you?

221
00:14:20,569 --> 00:14:23,864
We have come together
on this glorious day

222
00:14:24,031 --> 00:14:26,783
to wed Christy and Jeevan,

223
00:14:26,950 --> 00:14:31,580
who are here to build a foundation
of their marriage upon the earth,

224
00:14:31,747 --> 00:14:36,210
in the presence of a sacred fire
and among their family and friends.

225
00:14:39,880 --> 00:14:42,758
We are so late.
Has the ceremony started?

226
00:14:42,925 --> 00:14:44,259
- Yes, ma'am.
- Oh, no.

227
00:14:44,426 --> 00:14:46,512
- Okay.
- I told you to go ahead and go.

228
00:14:46,678 --> 00:14:50,098
I don't understand why you
couldn't leave the baby with Paige.

229
00:14:50,265 --> 00:14:52,559
When you're a mother,
you'll understand.

230
00:14:52,726 --> 00:14:55,312
That's assuming
I'm gonna have any eggs left.

231
00:14:55,479 --> 00:14:57,606
- How do you do this thing?
- Here.

232
00:15:00,067 --> 00:15:02,528
It's so nice to have
a man around the house.

233
00:15:02,694 --> 00:15:05,531
Yeah, except I think
I should still be after Barbas.

234
00:15:05,697 --> 00:15:09,409
Yeah, not until you can distinguish
between a demon and an Elder.

235
00:15:09,576 --> 00:15:10,786
You're stuck with us.

236
00:15:11,620 --> 00:15:13,747
- Paige? Hi...
- What are you doing?

237
