00:30:49,558 --> 00:30:52,728
- Not supposed to tell him that.
- You know me with secrets.

475
00:30:52,895 --> 00:30:55,105
I can't keep 'em.
How'd it go with Barbas?

476
00:30:55,272 --> 00:30:57,816
- Couldn't track him.
- You couldn't track him,

477
00:30:57,983 --> 00:31:00,110
not even with
those powers inside you?

478
00:31:00,277 --> 00:31:04,323
I know, strange, isn't it?
So where's Piper? Upstairs?

479
00:31:17,961 --> 00:31:20,422
- What happened?
- You're not gonna like it.

480
00:31:24,176 --> 00:31:27,137
You're not even gonna give 'em
a chance to cooperate?

481
00:31:27,304 --> 00:31:30,140
- Is that it?
- They had the chance. They didn't show.

482
00:31:30,307 --> 00:31:33,352
- We got a warrant.
- Doesn't give us the right to bust in.

483
00:31:33,519 --> 00:31:34,978
I want it to be a surprise.

484
00:31:39,149 --> 00:31:40,817
Got something you want to say?

485
00:31:46,240 --> 00:31:50,244
I'm gonna find out who this Chris
really was and what they're hiding.

486
00:31:50,410 --> 00:31:53,831
Now either you're with me...
or you're against me.

487
00:31:57,751 --> 00:32:00,170
This is why Piper
didn't want us to tell you.

488
00:32:00,337 --> 00:32:03,549
I'm gonna kill him.
Rip the world apart until I find Barbas.

489
00:32:03,715 --> 00:32:05,551
That's what we're worried about.

490
00:32:05,717 --> 00:32:08,303
- Calm down till we know the facts.
- What facts?

491
00:32:08,470 --> 00:32:11,515
- He went after one of my sons, again.
- He didn't get him.

492
00:32:11,682 --> 00:32:12,766
It doesn't matter.

493
00:32:12,933 --> 00:32:15,477
Police, freeze! Hands in the air!

494
00:32:19,356 --> 00:32:21,608
What the hell is wrong with you?

495
00:32:22,317 --> 00:32:24,194
Are you out of your mind?

496
00:32:27,865 --> 00:32:29,074
Yeah, I think he is.

497
00:32:29,241 --> 00:32:31,743
I just got the baby to sleep...

498
00:32:34,413 --> 00:32:35,455
What happened?

499
00:32:37,082 --> 00:32:38,292
Where's Leo?

500
00:32:57,102 --> 00:32:58,979
- Leo.
- Barbas. Where is he?

501
00:32:59,146 --> 00:33:01,148
- Barbas?
- How many times do you

502
00:33:01,315 --> 00:33:06,653
have to go through all this before you
realise they're all working together?

503
00:33:06,820 --> 00:33:08,822
Leo, don't do this.
You know better.

504
00:33:08,989 --> 00:33:12,659
He's after your boy, I'm after your boy,
they're all after your boy.

505
00:33:12,826 --> 00:33:16,246
- That's why it's your greatest fear.
- Where is he, damn it!

506
00:33:16,413 --> 00:33:20,542
- Listen to me, Leo! Don't do this!
- Kill him. Kill them all!

507
00:33:33,805 --> 00:33:35,974
My, my, my, my, my.

508
00:33:36,141 --> 00:33:40,312
What have we gone and done now?

509
00:33:49,696 --> 00:33:51,532
Thanks.

510
00:33:51,698 --> 00:33:53,200
Did you find Leo?

511
00:33:53,367 --> 00:33:56,328
- Where's Chris?
- He's with Wyatt in the nursery.

512
00:34:00,457 --> 00:34:02,960
- What happened?
- You find a spell to fix us?

513
00:34:03,126 --> 00:34:04,419
- Yeah, but...
- Cast it.

514
00:34:12,761 --> 00:34:17,266
We call upon the mortal ways
and Gods who guide but may not stay

515
00:34:17,432 --> 00:34:22,020
We seek those of divinity
to separate from and set them free

516
00:34:31,989 --> 00:34:33,073
Are you all right?

517
00:34:34,658 --> 00:34:35,909
Piper?

518
00:34:36,451 --> 00:34:38,495
Go get Phoebe
and then go get Barbas.

519
00:34:38,662 --> 00:34:40,747
We still don't know how to find him.

520
00:34:40,914 --> 00:34:44,168
I wounded him. You should
be able to scry with his blood.

521
00:34:56,471 --> 00:34:58,307
I killed another Elder.

522
00:34:58,473 --> 00:35:00,809
It's not your fault.
You were tricked.

523
00:35:00,976 --> 00:35:02,603
Was I?

524
00:35:05,230 --> 00:35:07,316
What have I become?

525
00:35:10,027 --> 00:35:13,322
It's okay. It's okay.

526
00:35:13,489 --> 00:35:15,824
Nobody else has to know.

527
00:35:21,205 --> 00:35:22,915
Just try to follow the light.

528
00:35:25,918 --> 00:35:28,170
I still don't think
this was a good idea.

529
00:35:28,337 --> 00:35:31,173
What did you want us to do,
send her to purgatory?

530
00:35:31,340 --> 00:35:34,259
We had to play it safe.
She's too suspicious already.

531
00:35:34,426 --> 00:35:37,262
Okay, but what if she
remembers what really happened?

532
00:35:37,429 --> 00:35:39,223
Look to your right.

533
00:35:40,682 --> 00:35:42,434
Focus.

534
00:35:43,602 --> 00:35:45,479
Get the C-collar and board.

535
00:35:49,566 --> 00:35:52,820
Do you remember what
you were doing here, Inspector?

536
00:35:54,404 --> 00:35:56,740
We came to search for something.

537
00:35:56,907 --> 00:35:59,243
Do you remember
what happened to you?

538
00:35:59,618 --> 00:36:03,747
She slipped. We're doing a lot of
redecorating, and she slipped and fell.

539
00:36:04,873 --> 00:36:07,042
Well, do you remember?

540
00:36:07,209 --> 00:36:08,502
I...

541
00:36:10,337 --> 00:36:11,713
No.

542
00:36:14,883 --> 00:36:16,510
Just take a deep breath.

543
00:36:16,677 --> 00:36:17,761
Good.

544
00:36:17,928 --> 00:36:21,598
- She remembers the search warrant.
- So? What is she gonna find?

545
00:36:21,765 --> 00:36:23,559
What's going on?

546
00:36:23,725 --> 00:36:26,186
Nothing. We have
everything under control.

547
00:36:26,353 --> 00:36:28,939
- What's up?
- We've got some work to do.

548
00:36:30,941 --> 00:36:35,028
Hey, why don't you
come on down, show yourself.

549
00:36:35,195 --> 00:36:40,826
All I want to do is thank you.
It was such a very good plan.

550
00:36:41,618 --> 00:36:44,788
I mean, it worked perfectly.

551
00:36:44,955 --> 00:36:47,416
So...

552
00:36:47,583 --> 00:36:51,336
How about we
go after the witches now?

553
00:36:51,503 --> 00:36:52,963
Works for us.

554
00:36:53,130 --> 00:36:55,799
Well, well, well, well, well,
what do you know?

555
00:36:55,966 --> 00:37:00,596
It really is true.
Just ask and ye shall receive.

556
00:37:00,762 --> 00:37:04,474
Of course, this lair
was supposed to be cloaked.

557
00:37:04,641 --> 00:37:08,187
Yeah, you should probably ask
your invisible friend about that.

558
00:37:08,353 --> 00:37:10,731
Yeah, well, maybe I will.

559
00:37:12,107 --> 00:37:15,027
Come to vanquish me, I see.

560
00:37:15,194 --> 00:37:17,571
What, again?

561
00:37:17,738 --> 00:37:19,615
I have one little question first.

562
00:37:19,781 --> 00:37:22,117
Why the baby?
What does that even get you?

563
00:37:22,284 --> 00:37:24,870
Oh, the baby, that...
that just gets me to you

564
00:37:25,037 --> 00:37:28,874
without the bodyguard.
By the way, how is old Leo anyway?

565
00:37:29,041 --> 00:37:31,752
Suffering nicely, I hope.

566
00:37:34,755 --> 00:37:38,050
I think we should
check your fears first.

567
00:37:38,217 --> 00:37:39,801
How charming.

568
00:37:39,968 --> 00:37:44,890
Your greatest fear is that
your nephews won't be safe...

569
00:37:45,807 --> 00:37:47,684
...from me. How touching.

570
00:37:47,851 --> 00:37:51,188
Of course, such a great fear
paralyses you.

571
00:37:51,355 --> 00:37:54,107
I can't believe you forgot about that.

572
00:37:54,274 --> 00:37:56,276
Oh, we didn't forget.

573
00:37:57,110 --> 00:38:00,656
We knew our greatest desire
would overcome our greatest fear.

574
00:38:00,823 --> 00:38:04,076
And our greatest desire
is to protect our nephews from you.

575
00:38:06,328 --> 00:38:08,831
You know I'll be back.

576
00:38:08,997 --> 00:38:11,416
Fear always come back!

577
00:38:13,085 --> 00:38:16,755
You set me up!

578
00:38:20,592 --> 00:38:22,761
I never get tired of seeing that.

579
00:38:22,928 --> 00:38:25,889
I wonder who he was talking to?

580
00:38:26,056 --> 00:38:29,059
I don't know,
and I don't wanna know.

581
00:38:53,292 --> 00:38:55,335
Making yourself comfortable, I see.

582
00:38:57,254 --> 00:38:58,922
Sorry.

583
00:38:59,089 --> 00:39:03,343
You know, you really don't have to
come in here bright and early any more.

584
00:39:03,510 --> 00:39:06,722
Otherwise,
it's not really a sabbatical.

585
00:39:06,889 --> 00:39:08,515
Yeah, I know.

586
00:39:10,434 --> 00:39:13,228
Actually, I'm gonna tell you the truth.

587
00:39:14,897 --> 00:39:19,026
After I met you, I wasn't so sure
I wanted to take the time off.

588
00:39:19,401 --> 00:39:21,528
Made quite an impression
on you, did I?

589
00:39:21,695 --> 00:39:23,405
No, not really.

590
00:39:23,572 --> 00:39:27,201
You kiss all the new employees
their first day on the job, do you?

591
00:39:27,367 --> 00:39:28,494
Yeah, well...

592
00:39:28,660 --> 00:39:29,953
That was...

593
00:39:30,120 --> 00:39:32,998
...you know,
not what you think it was.

594
00:39:33,165 --> 00:39:34,625
- Really?
- Yeah.

595
00:39:34,791 --> 00:39:36,877
And what do you think
I think it was?

596
00:39:37,044 --> 00:39:39,046
I don't know
what you think it was,

597
00:39:39,213 --> 00:39:41,965
but whatever you think it was,
it actually wasn't.

598
00:39:43,008 --> 00:39:47,638
Anyway, I thought I would wait until
this morning and read what you wrote

599
00:39:47,804 --> 00:39:50,641
and see if I was still
comfortable with my decision.

600
00:39:50,807 --> 00:39:53,227
- And?
- And I liked it.

601
00:39:53,393 --> 00:39:56,605
There was some good advice,
considering you're a guy.

602
00:39:56,772 --> 00:39:58,815
Well, thanks... I think.

603
00:39:58,982 --> 00:40:02,194
Of course, I wouldn't wanna
sully your good name.

604
00:40:02,361 --> 00:40:04,112
You'd better not.

605
00:40:05,531 --> 00:40:07,616
Good luck.

606
00:40:08,659 --> 00:40:10,577
Hey, for whatever it's worth...

607
00:40:11,703 --> 00:40:13,789
...you're a pretty damn good kisser.

608
00:40:13,956 --> 00:40:17,042
Even though
it didn't mean anything.

609
00:40:24,383 --> 00:40:27,177
I'm so tired.
I didn't sleep at all last night.

610
00:40:27,344 --> 00:40:29,680
And it's not even because of Barbas.

611
00:40:29,847 --> 00:40:31,598
Pray tell.

612
00:40:31,765 --> 00:40:35,686
It's the whole Magic School thing.
It's got me really depressed.

613
00:40:36,103 --> 00:40:39,147
I don't know why the Elders
are just shutting it down.

614
00:40:39,314 --> 00:40:43,318
Well, they can do whatever they want.
That's why they're them.

615
00:40:43,527 --> 00:40:46,155
Yeah, well, it's not fair.

616
00:40:46,321 --> 00:40:48,782
Well, who's gonna stop them?

617
00:40:48,949 --> 00:40:50,367
I am.

618
00:40:51,910 --> 00:40:53,996
- What?
- Yeah.

619
00:40:54,163 --> 00:40:57,374
Magic's the best thing
that has ever happened to me, right?

620
00:40:57,541 --> 00:40:59,835
I mean, other than you guys.
No offence.

621
00:41:00,002 --> 00:41:04,173
But you guys did happen to me at
the same time that magic happened to me.

622
00:41:04,339 --> 00:41:06,216
- So if you count it...
- Rambling.

623
00:41:06,383 --> 00:41:07,593
Right.

624
00:41:07,759 --> 00:41:10,804
Aside from Gideon,
the school is a great thing, right?

625
00:41:10,971 --> 00:41:14,558
I think I'm gonna do it. I'm gonna
get back to my magical roots.

626
00:41:14,725 --> 00:41:17,102
I think that's a good idea.

627
00:41:17,269 --> 00:41:19,146
Any idea how you're gonna do it?

628
00:41:20,564 --> 00:41:22,649
Not a clue.

629
00:41:23,108 --> 00:41:25,777
Oh, my goodness...

630
00:41:25,944 --> 00:41:28,864
Are you going outside?
With them?

631
00:41:29,031 --> 00:41:31,116
Yes, I am.

632
00:41:31,283 --> 00:41:34,161
May I go, or do you want to
tease me some more about it?

633
00:41:34,328 --> 00:41:37,498
I'd like to tease you more,
but I'll wait till you get back.

634
00:41:37,789 --> 00:41:38,957
What changed?

635
00:41:39,124 --> 00:41:41,752
Well, sharing a body
with the ultimate mother...

636
00:41:41,919 --> 00:41:44,129
- I got a few tips.
- Like what?

637
00:41:44,296 --> 00:41:46,715
Like I can't protect them
from everything.

638
00:41:46,882 --> 00:41:49,426
Or I'll probably end up
making them neurotic.

639
00:41:49,593 --> 00:41:51,803
We don't need
more of those around here.

640
00:41:51,970 --> 00:41:56,475
No, so we're just gonna have to
go out and brave the big, bad world.

641
00:41:57,392 --> 00:41:59,478
What about Leo? Is he gonna join?

642
00:41:59,645 --> 00:42:01,688
No, he's still...

643
00:42:01,855 --> 00:42:03,941
...dealing with some stuff.

644
00:42:15,118 --> 00:42:17,621
Barbas was right.

645
00:42:18,997 --> 00:42:22,918
Killing him doesn't kill
the pain of betrayal.

646
00:42:24,545 --> 00:42:27,381
Who the hell are you?
What do you want?

647
00:42:27,548 --> 00:42:29,466
What do we want?

648
00:42:29,633 --> 00:42:31,385
We want you!

